<ItacAcademyItem AcademyId="0100" RecordId="021-000004905"><Name>Veneziana (Seconda Accademia)</Name><City CityId="35"><CityItalianName>Venezia</CityItalianName><CityEnglishName>Venice</CityEnglishName><CityLatinName>Venetiae</CityLatinName></City><EmblemDescription>Palisade of wood such as is used for foundations in Venice, with hoisting apparatus</EmblemDescription><EmblemImage ImageId="55259">021-000004905_55259_1.jpg</EmblemImage><Motto>Hinc attollere moles</Motto><StartDate>1594</StartDate><EndDate>1608</EndDate><DateText>1594-1608</DateText><Notes>Main sources for this Academy is Giovanni Pellegrini, Giornale dell`italiana letteratura (1812), which reports the Academy laws and list of members. See also Michele Maylender, Storia delle Accademie d`Italia, vol. V, pp. 444-46, and Paolo Ulvioni, `Accademie e cultura in Italia dalla Controriforma all`Arcadia : Il caso veneziano`, in Libri &amp; Documenti, 5 (1979), pp. 21-75.    Publications related to this Academy, but not in British Library collections, include: Lucii Scarani academici Veneti Ad serenissimum Marinum Grimanum Venetiarum principem. Gratulatio (Venetiis: apud Io. Battistam Ciottum, 1595);    Lucii Scarani academici Veneti Princeps, seu Laudatio Pascalis Ciconiae, olim serenissimae reipublicae Venetae principis, Academiae mandato habita (Venetiis: apud Rubertum Meiettum, 1595);    Oratione del sig. Gio. Battista Leoni presidente dell`Academia Venetiana recitata da lui nell`essequie dell`ill.mo sig. Giulio Savorgnano conte di Belgrado ..  (In Venetia: appresso Andrea Muschio, 1595). Fabio Paolini, De pace oratio Fabii Paulini habita Venetijs Id. Sept. in Veneta Academia (Venetiis: Georgius Angelerius excudebat, 1599). On other publications possibly related to this Academy, see also Palo Zaja, Marinelli Lucrezia, in DBI.</Notes><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20009" RecordId="022-000007485"><Name>Leoni,Giovanni Battista,,1542? - 1613?</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><It